    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-01-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-02-17T15:25:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Helping America Hear Act of 2007 - Requires each federal employee health benefits plan to provide coverage for at least two hearing aids every three years, except that such plan need not cover more than $2,500 for hearing aids for any individual in any three-year period. </p> <p>Amends the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (ERISA) to require a group health plan that provides hospital and surgical benefits to also provide such hearing aid coverage.</p> <p>Amends the Public Health Service Act to require health insurance offered in the individual market to provide such coverage.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
